headline: 5 Must-Read Analyst Questions From U.S. Cellular’s Q2 Earnings Call
summary: U.S. Cellular’s second quarter results were greeted positively by the market as the company delivered revenue and profit ahead of Wall Street’s expectations, despite a modest year-on-year sales decline. Leadership attributed the outperformance to disciplined execution during a period of significant transformation, with CEO Walter Carlson highlighting the successful close of the T-Mobile transaction and the resulting shift toward a focused fiber and tower infrastructure strategy.
